@node VPN for IMDb
@section VPN for IMDb

@vindex zotra-extras-use-mullvad-p
The Internet Movie Database (IMDb) returns metadata that may vary based on the geographic location of the request. The user option @code{zotra-extras-use-mullvad-p} controls whether @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} routes IMDb requests through a specific Mullvad VPN server to ensure consistent results (for example, fetching English-language metadata by connecting through New York).

When set to non-nil, and when the URL or search string passed to @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} matches @samp{imdb.com}, the command calls @code{mullvad-connect-to-website} with the @samp{"IMDb"} website identifier before fetching data. This requires the @samp{mullvad} package and appropriate configuration of @code{mullvad-websites-and-cities} and @code{mullvad-cities-and-servers}. Specifically, @code{mullvad-websites-and-cities} must contain a cons cell like @samp{("IMDb" . "New York")} and @code{mullvad-cities-and-servers} must map that city to a server like @samp{("New York" . "us-nyc-wg-601")}.

The default value is @code{nil}, meaning all requests use the direct internet connection.

