@node Ebib post-processing
@section Ebib post-processing

@findex zotra-extras-open-in-ebib
The function @code{zotra-extras-open-in-ebib} handles the workflow of opening a newly added entry in @samp{ebib}. It launches @samp{ebib} if needed, switches to the correct database, reloads it, sorts entries by timestamp, navigates to the new entry, saves the database (to persist the sorted order), and prompts the user to verify that the entry type and key are correct before invoking @code{ebib-extras-process-entry} for further processing.

@node Bib@TeX{} cleanup
@section Bib@TeX{} cleanup

@findex zotra-extras-after-add-process-bibtex
@findex zotra-extras-fix-octal-sequences
The function @code{zotra-extras-after-add-process-bibtex} performs several cleanup steps on a newly added Bib@TeX{} entry in the current buffer. It converts @samp{titleaddon} fields to @samp{journaltitle}, sets a @samp{timestamp} field using the @samp{ebib} timestamp format, fixes octal encoding sequences, cleans the entry using @code{org-ref-clean-bibtex-entry}, replaces EAF URLs via @code{tlon-cleanup-eaf-replace-urls}, and records the entry key in @code{zotra-extras-most-recent-bibkey}.

The function @code{zotra-extras-fix-octal-sequences} addresses a specific issue where Zotero-imported Bib@TeX{} entries contain octal escape sequences (such as @samp{\302\267} for a middle dot) that Emacs does not decode automatically. The function iterates over a range of possible octal sequences and replaces each one with its corresponding UTF-8 character.

@node Fetching fields
@section Fetching fields

@findex zotra-extras-fetch-field
The function @code{zotra-extras-fetch-field} retrieves the value of a single FIELD (such as @samp{"title"} or @samp{"author"}) from the bibliographic metadata for a given URL-OR-SEARCH-STRING, without adding the full entry to any bibliography file. It fetches the raw Bib@TeX{} data via @code{zotra-get-entry-1}, parses it in a temporary buffer using @samp{bibtex-mode}, and extracts the requested field. Optional arguments allow suppressing errors (IGNORE-ERRORS) and setting a custom TIMEOUT@. This function is useful when you need metadata for programmatic purposes without side effects.

@node Org protocol handler
@section Org protocol handler

@findex zotra-extras-protocol
The function @code{zotra-extras-protocol} handles @samp{org-protocol://zotra?...} requests, enabling you to add bibliographic entries directly from a web browser via a bookmarklet or browser extension. The INFO plist may contain @samp{:url}, @samp{:bibfile}, @samp{:format}, and @samp{:title} keys. The function extracts these and delegates to @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} (@ref{Adding entries}).

The protocol is registered automatically when the package is loaded, adding an entry to @code{org-protocol-protocol-alist}.

@node Adding multiple URLs
@section Adding multiple URLs

@findex zotra-extras-add-multiple-urls
The function @code{zotra-extras-add-multiple-urls} is the non-interactive workhorse behind @code{zotra-extras-add-multiple-urls-from-file} (@ref{Batch processing}). It accepts a list of URLS and a BIBFILE, saves all open @samp{ebib} databases, then iterates through the URLs calling @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} for each with DO-NOT-OPEN set. After all entries are added, it opens the bibliography in @samp{ebib} and sorts by timestamp.

